@bolkedebruin, I've added tests to specifically test the outcomes of the actions performed by the models involved in the flask_admin TaskInstance model view of the Airflow UI. I tried to access the endpoint for updating the data directly ('/admin/taskinstance/action/') but it looks like flask_admin responds with a 405 response code when attempting to hit the endpoint outside of flask_admin (Hitting the endpoint would have followed the standard currently established in the tests.www.test_views module). However, I was able to set up tests to test the flask_admin model itself, which, in combination with the flask_admin escape function usage, should provide the test case we're looking for. 

One thing to point out is that this is effectively integration testing between the airflow SQLAlchemy Models and the flask_admin package. I'm not sure how integration testing usually works within airflow, but as far as the tests go between airflows SQLAlchemy Models and flask_admin (the main entry point for users for manipulation of airflow job meta data such as dag_runs, task_instances, etc.) this could serve as a template for a greater suite of tests regarding that functionality. 

Anyway, please take a look at the update to the tests and the reasoning I gave in the JIRA ticket and previous post regarding why this code should be merged. Happy to respond to design considerations.

@bolkedebruin I've added a unit test for the logging change and fixed the travis build (apologies for calling you prematurely, will be more careful in the future).

I've also put some work in on the blog post on the operator. Would it be ok to send it over when I have a rough draft?

Thanks for the review!

